  "text": "# HTTP Connection Manager Route Matching Implementation in Envoy\n\n## Overview\n\nThe HTTP connection manager (HCM) route matching in Envoy v1.31.2 is implemented across multiple C++ source files that work together to:\n1. **Virtual host selection**: Match incoming requests to virtual hosts based on domain/authority headers\n2. **Route matching algorithm**: Match routes within a virtual host based on path, method, headers, and other criteria\n3. **Route action dispatch**: Dispatch matched routes to appropriate upstream clusters with configured transformations\n\n## Core Architecture\n\n### HTTP Connection Manager Configuration\n**Files:**\n- `source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h` - Factory and configuration for HCM filter\n- `source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.cc` - Implementation\n\n**Key Classes:**\n- `HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory` - Creates HCM filter instances from protobuf config\n- `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` - Holds HCM configuration including route config provider\n\n**Responsibility:** Creates and manages the HTTP connection manager filter that orchestrates route matching through a route config provider.\n\n### Route Configuration and Matching\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/config_impl.h` - Core route matching classes and interfaces\n- `source/common/router/config_impl.cc` - Implementation of route matching algorithm\n\n**Key Classes and Their Roles:**\n\n#### 1. **ConfigImpl** (overall route configuration wrapper)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:1653-1706` and `config_impl.cc:2286-2300+`\n   - Wraps route configuration and delegates to RouteMatcher\n   - Entry point: `ConfigImpl::route()` method\n\n#### 2. **RouteMatcher** (virtual host selection)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:1532-1576` and `config_impl.cc:2051-2171`\n   - **Virtual host selection algorithm** (lines 2113-2159):\n     - `RouteMatcher::findVirtualHost()`: Fast path for default vhost, exact domain match, wildcard suffix match (*domain.com), wildcard prefix match (domain.*)\n     - Uses lowest-cost-first matching: exact > prefix wildcards > suffix wildcards > default\n   - **Route matching dispatch** (lines 2161-2171):\n     - `RouteMatcher::route()`: Finds virtual host, then delegates to virtual host for route matching\n   - **Domain matching features**:\n     - Exact domain matching: `virtual_hosts_` hash map (line 1561)\n     - Wildcard suffix matching: `wildcard_virtual_host_suffixes_` (line 1571) - matches \"*.example.com\"\n     - Wildcard prefix matching: `wildcard_virtual_host_prefixes_` (line 1572) - matches \"api.*\"\n     - Default virtual host: `default_virtual_host_` (line 1574) - fallback for \"*\"\n     - Port-aware matching: `ignorePortInHostMatching()` (line 1558)\n\n#### 3. **VirtualHostImpl** (routes collection for a virtual host)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:384-417` and `config_impl.cc:1870-2028`\n   - **Route matching logic** (lines 1978-2028):\n     - SSL requirement checking (lines 1993-1999)\n     - Matcher tree evaluation (lines 2001-2023) - uses new matcher API for complex matching\n     - Legacy route iteration (lines 2026-2027) - fallback for traditional routes\n   - `getRouteFromEntries()`: Main entry point that checks SSL requirements and evaluates matcher tree or iterates routes\n   - `getRouteFromRoutes()`: Iterates through route list and matches each route (lines 1941-1975)\n\n#### 4. **CommonVirtualHostImpl** (shared virtual host data)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:251-377` and `config_impl.cc:1734+`\n   - Holds shared configuration for virtual host (rate limits, CORS, retry policies, etc.)\n   - Virtual cluster matching: `virtualClusterFromEntries()` (lines 2178-2191)\n\n#### 5. **Route Entry Implementations** (specific route matchers)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h` with implementations in `config_impl.cc`\n   - Each implements the `Matchable` interface (lines 65-82):\n     - **RouteEntryImplBase** (base class, line 639-641) - Base for all route types\n     - **PrefixRouteEntryImpl** - Matches by path prefix\n     - **PathRouteEntryImpl** (line 1338) - Matches exact path\n     - **RegexRouteEntryImpl** - Matches path with regex\n     - **ConnectRouteEntryImpl** - Matches CONNECT method\n     - **PathSeparatedPrefixRouteEntryImpl** - Matches by path segments\n     - **UriTemplateMatcherRouteEntryImpl** - Matches by URI template\n   - Each implements: `matches(headers, stream_info, random_value)` virtual method\n   - Route matching includes: path matching, header matching, method matching, query parameter matching\n\n#### 6. **Matcher Tree Support** (for complex matching)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:1471-1526` and `config_impl.cc`\n   - **RouteMatchAction** (line 1478) - Action for single route matches\n   - **RouteListMatchAction** (line 1503) - Action for multiple route candidates\n   - **RouteMatchActionFactory** (line 1489) - Factory for route actions in matcher tree\n   - Uses `Matcher::MatchTreeFactory` to build and evaluate matcher trees\n   - Matcher tree enables complex conditional routing (nested conditions)\n\n#### 7. **CommonConfigImpl** (shared route configuration)\n   - Located in: `source/common/router/config_impl.h:1581-1648` and `config_impl.cc:2193-2275`\n   - Holds global route configuration (internal-only headers, request/response header parsers, shadow policies)\n   - Per-filter configuration management\n\n### Router Filter\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/router.h` - Router filter header\n- `source/common/router/router.cc` - Router filter implementation\n\n**Key Classes:**\n- `Filter` (HTTP filter) - Main router filter that processes HTTP requests\n- `FilterConfig` - Configuration holder for the router filter\n- `FilterUtility` - Helper utilities for the router filter\n\n**Route Matching Invocation:**\n- Located in: `source/common/router/router.cc:430-463` (decodeHeaders method)\n- **Line 454**: `route_ = callbacks_->route();` - Calls HTTP connection manager to perform route matching\n- Route matching happens in the HTTP connection manager context via route config provider\n- After match, filter dispatches request to appropriate upstream cluster (lines 505-515)\n- Handles direct responses (lines 466-489)\n\n### Dynamic Route Configuration (RDS)\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/rds_impl.h` - RDS route config provider interface\n- `source/common/router/rds_impl.cc` - RDS implementation for dynamic route updates\n- `source/common/router/scoped_rds.h` - Scoped RDS for dynamic virtual hosts (VHDS)\n- `source/common/router/scoped_rds.cc` - Scoped RDS implementation\n\n**Responsibility:** Manages dynamic route configuration updates from control plane\n\n### Route Config Providers\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/static_route_provider_impl.h` - Static route provider\n- `source/common/router/static_route_provider_impl.cc` - Implementation\n- `source/common/router/route_config_update_receiver_impl.h` - Route update receiver\n- `source/common/router/route_config_update_receiver_impl.cc` - Implementation\n\n## Route Matching Flow\n\n1. **HTTP Request arrives** → HTTP Connection Manager\n2. **Virtual Host Selection** (`RouteMatcher::findVirtualHost()`):\n   - Extract Host/Authority header\n   - Exact match in `virtual_hosts_` map\n   - Suffix wildcard match in `wildcard_virtual_host_suffixes_`\n   - Prefix wildcard match in `wildcard_virtual_host_prefixes_`\n   - Default virtual host as fallback\n3. **Route Matching** (`VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries()`):\n   - Check SSL requirements\n   - If matcher tree exists: evaluate matcher tree to get candidate routes\n   - If legacy routes: iterate through routes list\n4. **Route Entry Matching** (`RouteEntryImplBase::matches()`):\n   - Path matching (prefix, exact, regex, URI template)\n   - Header matching\n   - Method matching\n   - Query parameter matching\n   - Runtime matching\n5. **Route Action Dispatch**:\n   - Get cluster from matched route entry\n   - Apply retry policies\n   - Apply header transformations\n   - Forward request to upstream\n\n## Key Matching Features\n\n- **Virtual Host Matching**: Domain-based routing with wildcard support and port-aware matching\n- **Path Matching**: Multiple algorithms (prefix, exact, regex, URI template, path-separated-prefix)\n- **Header Matching**: Match on request headers (case-insensitive or case-sensitive)\n- **Method Matching**: HTTP method filtering\n- **Query Parameter Matching**: Match query parameters in URL\n- **Runtime Matching**: Configuration-driven feature flags\n- **Matcher Tree**: Complex conditional matching for advanced scenarios\n- **Direct Response**: Generate responses without routing to backend\n- **SSL/TLS Requirements**: Enforce HTTPS based on virtual host configuration\n\nThis comprehensive implementation provides Envoy with a flexible, high-performance route matching system that supports both simple domain/path-based routing and complex conditional matching scenarios.\n"
}

