e/common/router/router.cc:430-463` (decodeHeaders method)\n- **Line 454**: `route_ = callbacks_->route();` - Calls HTTP connection manager to perform route matching\n- Route matching happens in the HTTP connection manager context via route config provider\n- After match, filter dispatches request to appropriate upstream cluster (lines 505-515)\n- Handles direct responses (lines 466-489)\n\n### Dynamic Route Configuration (RDS)\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/rds_impl.h` - RDS route config provider interface\n- `source/common/router/rds_impl.cc` - RDS implementation for dynamic route updates\n- `source/common/router/scoped_rds.h` - Scoped RDS for dynamic virtual hosts (VHDS)\n- `source/common/router/scoped_rds.cc` - Scoped RDS implementation\n\n**Responsibility:** Manages dynamic route configuration updates from control plane\n\n### Route Config Providers\n**Files:**\n- `source/common/router/static_route_provider_impl.h` - Static route provider\n- `source/common/router/static_route_provider_impl.cc` - Implementation\n- `source/common/router/route_config_update_receiver_impl.h` - Route update receiver\n- `source/common/router/route_config_update_receiver_impl.cc` - Implementation\n\n## Route Matching Flow\n\n1. **HTTP Request arrives** → HTTP Connection Manager\n2. **Virtual Host Selection** (`RouteMatcher::findVirtualHost()`):\n   - Extract Host/Authority header\n   - Exact match in `virtual_hosts_` map\n   - Suffix wildcard match in `wildcard_virtual_host_suffixes_`\n   - Prefix wildcard match in `wildcard_virtual_host_prefixes_`\n   - Default virtual host as fallback\n3. **Route Matching** (`VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries()`):\n   - Check SSL requirements\n   - If matcher tree exists: evaluate matcher tree to get candidate routes\n   - If legacy routes: iterate through routes list\n4. **Route Entry Matching** (`RouteEntryImplBase::matches()`):\n   - Path matching (prefix, exact, regex, URI template)\n   - Header matching\n   - Method matching\n   - Query